    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-05T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-05T19:00:00-05:00" n="5"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710 Consultation 3A/521: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-05T21:00:00-03:00"
                            >January 5, 1944—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. For Duggan from Spaeth. With further reference to our cable 22, 5th,<note
                        n="15" xml:id="d5fn15">Not printed.</note> both resolution and summary of
                    replies were approved unanimously although Chilean member<note n="16"
                        xml:id="d5fn16">Alfredo Rodriguez MacIver.</note> initially opposed
                    resolution and sought to delay action, informing me privately that he wanted
                    time to consult his Government. Argentine<note n="17" xml:id="d5fn17">The
                        Argentine member of the Committee was Guillermo de Achával.</note> was
                    absent. [Spaeth.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
